(Self, Self) -> ClosedRange<Self>`](/documentation/swift/autoreleasingunsafemutablepointer/)Returns a closed range that contains both of its bounds.[`static func ..< (Self) -> PartialRangeUpTo<Self>`](/documentation/swift/autoreleasingunsafemutablepointer/)Returns a partial range up to, but not including, its upper bound.[`static func ..< (Self, Self) -> Range<Self>`](/documentation/swift/autoreleasingunsafemutablepointer/)Returns a half-open range that contains its lower bound but not its upper bound.[`static func > (Self, Self) -> Bool`](/documentation/swift/autoreleasingunsafemutablepointer/_(_:_:)-24u5j)Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the value of the first argument is greater than that of the second argument.[`static func < (Self, Self) -> Bool`](/documentation/swift/autoreleasingunsafemutablepointer/_(_:_:)-fe5k)Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the value of the first argument is less than that of the second argument.[`static func <= (Self, Self) -> Bool`](/documentation/swift/autoreleasingunsafemutablepointer/_=(_:_:)-1ihk)Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the value of the first argument is less than or equal to that of the second argument.[`static func >= (Self, Self) -> Bool`](/documentation/swift/autoreleasingunsafemutablepointer/_=(_:_:)-8lyi4)Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the value of the first argument is greater than or equal to that of the second argument.
